  "body": "Hello. Last days I'm trying to check how my project would work with block from the past. And I decided to check the blocknumber that I have forking mainnet in Hardhat. As I see in docs hardhat forks the latest block : \"Hardhat Network will by default fork from the latest mainnet block\". But what I received:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst provider = new ethers.providers.JsonRpcProvider(\"https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/%22);\r\n\r\nconst { ethers } = require(\"hardhat\")\r\n\r\nblock = await provider.getBlockNumber()\r\n```\r\n16034315 from provider.getBlockNumber //current block from provider\r\n\r\n`block = await ethers.provider.getBlockNumber()`\r\n16034309 from ethers.provider.getBlockNumber // minus 6 blocks\r\n\r\nAnd if I understand it correctly `ethers.provider.getBlockNumber()` shows a forking mainnet.\r\nWhy do I have this difference in 6 blocks if I didn't pin a block from the past?",
